<Review>Linda's Coffee House is my favorite neighborhood coffee shop! They offer a little bit of everything from breakfast burritos, breakfast sandwiches, breakfast plates, donuts, pastries, sandwiches, and all kinds of beverages. My favorite things to order are the low carb tortilla wrap, steak breakfast burrito, and the protein shake (40g of protein)!

Their food is made fresh to order, their coffee is spot on, and their prices are extremely reasonable. They do get a little crowded on the weekends, but I've noticed it a little less crowded lately (maybe due to Covid)? You can call in your order in advance too so you don't want to wait. I recently called in an order for 10 breakfast burritos and they were ready within 30 minutes.

If you're in the mood for a quick breakfast or some donuts, definitely check out Linda's Coffee House!</Review>< pictures>

<user_id>108760604956499925166< /user_id><Name>Tyrone Villacrusis<//Name><date>1592063043742</date><Rating>4<//Rating>< text>
I have been calling a few places to get one of my door handles re-done because of a paint chip and I found this place. I gave it a try and was quoted by Edgar who was awesome! I ended up getting my car a day earlier than expected. However, it would have been a 5-star review if I didn't have a problem after I picked up my car. Turned it on and found a keyless system issue which I never had this issue before as my car was just a week old. It's just weird that they didn't notice this when they drove it back to the parking lot after they called me that it's ready to be picked it up.

I brought this up and they fixed it. All in all, it was great but had I not checked my car prior to leaving the lot, this would have been a longer conversation. In the end, the customer service was great except for this one instance. I'll give them the benefit of the doubt that maybe it was just a one-off and they didn't notice it.

I would definitely consider this place again in the future.</text>

< Review>
A couple people mentioned Maaco as well as seeing ads on TV.  My Wife wanted to get our Toyota Tundra painted because it was an eye sore parked in front of our home. Parking it in Santa Cruz for long periods of time had eaten away the paint on the hood and roof.
Edgar, at the Stockton St San Jose location who was our sales guy quoted over $3k when we first brought it over for an estimate. We got him down to $2600 including some body work (scuffs minor and one major dents) along with new rubber rain guard trim around all the windows.
The work was done two days early and is pretty good except for a few small dents still showing through the new paint job. After taking the truck to a well known body shop and getting a quote for $10k, $2600 seemed good.
It comes with a 2 year no questions asked warrantee as well.
I‚Äôd use Maaco for auto paint again and might  consider them for dents as they come along. I drive a lot...< /Review>

<Response>None<//Response>< text>
I contacted Social to see if they could accommodate a surprise graduation party for my daughter & her two friends.  I initially spoke to Andrew, who subsequently referred me to Veronica.  Veronica is nothing short of a ROCK STAR and a pleasure to know. Not only were we able to reserve the entire patio for the party, but Veronica made sure the audio/visual was ready so that everyone could watch the virtual graduation. Additionally, they allowed us to decorate the patio with the girl's school colors and graduation decorations.

One would think with so many guests service might have been a little sketchy but not at SOCIAL.  The service we received was outstanding and honestly some of the best service I have ever experienced in a restaurant setting. Our food and drink orders were delivered almost as fast as we ordered them.  Everything we ordered was fresh hot, and delicious.

Veronica and her team made sure every detail was spot-on.  They made us feel at home, and the girls had a fantastic time.  I would recommend SOCIAL to anyone looking for a fun, casual, sexy place to eat, drink, or just vibe and check out the scenery.  I love this place and will most certainly make it my regular spot.

Thank you, Andrew, Veronica, and the SOCIAL team, for making sure our daughter's virtual graduation ceremony and party were a success.  I'll see you soon.< /text>

I never do reviews, and I certainly didn't expect to give a five star review for a car rental place that sells cars...but here it is.

Dreading buying a used car, I didn't have very high expectations of my experience based on past experiences buying used.

However, I was very impressed with Courtney Chew, the agent who assisted me.

She was extremely attentive to my needs for a car, was very patient and made me feel very comfortable.  She answered all my questions (and I had a lot) and helped me not only with financing that went way above my expectations, but she had found me a newer model of the exact car I drove!  I thought that was amazing - but she worked together with another gentleman there at her branch, I believe his name is Derek, who with her went way over and above my expectations.

I ended up purchasing a 2019 Nissan Sentra four door - with 24k miles - for $4,000 UNDER MSRP!!  It was in my favorite color - red - and drives like a dream!  My mechanic was impressed with the excellent condition of the car, and I can't believe my payments are $100 less than the payments of my former Chevy Spark!  I grabbed a handful of Courtney's business cards and am telling all my friends to go there for their next car.  I can't believe how smooth the process was - and how above and beyond they went there.  Courtney's associate even shared half his sandwich with me because we were going a little longer than expected because he and Courtney were trying to get the best financing for me.  (Which they did!)  Who does that!!

Anyway - thank you Courtney, you have won a customer for life, and I'm telling everyone who will listen to go to Enterprise and ask for you!!  You are the BEST!!<//Text>

<user_id>112426412800237141121< /user_id><Text>My wife and I purchased a 10-seat passenger van from Enterprise in Redwood City (2013 Ford E-350 XLT).  Our sales consultant, Frank Higgins, was uniformly excellent. He gave us an unhurried tour of the van and a test drive, reviewed the van's features, answered some fairly detailed questions and explained Enterprise's used car program. We discussed the rationale for its pricing openly (about $1K below its KBB).  When we decided to buy this van, Frank and his team were efficient in initiating and processing a good loan for us. At no point was there the kind of pressure one might anticipate with the caricature of a used car sale.  That said, if you are looking for a haggling experience I don't think this venue is for you. Others might be able to push back on this, but my sense was that the price is the price.

Our experience supports Enterprise's claim of post-sale service. A couple weeks after purchase, the van's battery failed.  Frank was quickly responsive in helping us navigate to a service partner, and the problem was quickly resolved.

So, our experience has been overall very positive. I recommend them.</Text>< rating>
5</rating>

<review>A little late on this, but I think I have had sufficient time to look back on my purchase. I was in the market for a used car back in September of 2018. This was gonna be my first car, so I was a little cautious about being ripped off or ending up with a bad purchase. After doing my (exhaustive) online research on dealers and shops in the area, I decided to give Enterprise Car Sales a try since they seemed to have a pretty good selection at reasonable prices.

Booking an appointment was easy and I met up with Joshua in their office. We went for a test drive in the car I'd previewed online and I was given the flexibility and freedom to try different roads and play around with the car's controls without having to worry about being rebuked. After the drive, Joshua explained to me the entire buying process. He suggested I make a decision soon since their cars get sold pretty quick (which seemed fair based on my comparision of their online catalog over several days), but wasn't pushy or disingenuous.

I ended up booking an appointment a few days later to purchase the same car. The entire process took only a couple hours and was super smooth - everyone was very professional, quick and friendly. Joshua even drove me to the bank and back so I could pick up my money order. He also connected me with a AAA agent to set up my insurance. Several signatures and couple hours later, I was off with my first car!

I highly recommend Enterprise if you're looking for a car, new or used, and I'll definitely have them as my first preference for any purchases in the future!<//review>< Pics>

< Review>
I unexpectedly found myself in the market for a new car after a collision earlier this year. To be honest, buying a car from a rental agency didn't appeal to me at all. People are really hard on their rentals, after all it's not theirs. When I went in to rent a car in the meantime while figuring out what I was going to do, I saw a newer Dodge Charger and asked if I could rent that one, and that's when they told me that it was for sale, not for rent. I said that I may be interested and they promised to have someone call me over the weekend and they did.
Before they handed me the keys for a test drive they explained to me how Enterprise Car Sales works, in that they're more interested in getting me into a car that I love and suits my needs and expectations than the sale. Enterprise really means it when they say that they have "no haggle pricing", I tried and a day later my husband tried, to test that theory. What made me interested in buying a car from THEM versus a dealership was that if I wasn't happy within 7 days I could return the car with no hassle (except for a small $250 fee). Although I couldn't take the Charger to my mechanic before the sale, that 7 day window was adequate for me. I test drove the Charger on the Sunday before Presidents Day (which was my birthday), fell in love, and decided to sleep on the decision. They didn't pressure me to sign on the dotted line that day.
Enterprise Car Sales worked some customer service magic and got in touch with my bank ON PRESIDENTS DAY (Banks are closed) and helped push my loan through on that holiday.

I never thought that buying a car could be a good experience, based on my past purchases. They do have some cool security upgrades that you can get with your warranty package. Buying a car from them was actually an enjoyable experience. When going to a car dealership it can be like preparing yourself for a financial and emotional battle, and I had none of that with Enterprise. I actually liked the car sales guy!  I've been enjoying my Dodge Charger for 9 months now, nothing has gone wrong with it, my mechanic reviewed everything possible, including looking to see if Enterprise deleted anything weird from the car about the car. He informed me that I got a good deal and I've been happy ever since.<//Review>

<Time>1480836357723< /Time><Rating>4</Rating><Review>Like everyone, we had a bit of an opinion regarding buying rental car.
In the end, the experience was very good, despite some extra hurdle, as explained below.

Overall, our reseller Tinh was very concerned about making us happy and confident with our choice. He really did a great job and was very friendly and considerate.

The car we were interested in was all great and a great deal.
But after a thorough inspection, some things needed to be repaired before the purchase.
Tinh really took action in solving all these little things, though I had to put a significant time-effort to organize everything.
However, it is really worth inspecting the car in the very details and I recommend to bring the car of interest to an independent mechanics for a check up before to conclude any deal.

Our car needed some fixing, the cost of which were eventually taken care of by Enterprise car sales. This was nice but it does mean that one has to organize a proper inspection before to sign a contract, otherwise, it's for your own!

Overall, we are happy with out vehicle and we thank Tinh for his help.</Review>< Pictures>

<text>Sadly, this place didn't deliver to the level that the other reviews eluded to. I brought a Pixel 2 XL here for a screen repair on a cracked screen. The phone was only 12 days old. When dropping off the phone I was immediately weirded out after seeing the level of damage that was reported. According to this company, a 12 day old device had scratches in more than 5 areas. The device was visually perfect other than the screen.

The screen repair was complete and I picked up my device. I told the team I trusted them when I picked it up. After booting up the device, I noticed there was something putting pressure on the screen from below. This was certainly not there prior to the screen repair. And, obvious enough that anyone who turned the device on would have noticed it. After a few hours went by, the pressure turned into an area of broken pixels in the screen. For a company certified to perform Google device repairs, I'm less than impressed. At this point I'd rather go to another company, or do it myself, since they cannot replace the screen without creating more imperfections. I've given the company an opportunity to refund for the repair, which they have declined. They have put the blame on Google even though this is obviously the fault of repair.

**UPDATE**

Disappointed with the response to my review. Clearly they are trying to put the blame on me as to why my screen had an imperfection. I have timestamped photos to prove that this was due to their repair! This company is an absolute joke. They even told me to bring it in for them to replace the screen. I declined. Spend your money elsewhere.<//text>< Pictures>

< review>
I have a Google Pixel phone that is under warranty and having battery problems. Google tech support sent me to this store to perform the warranty work on my Pixel. I called them to find out how long the repair usually takes so that I could make arrangements for another phone if it was going to take very long. I use this phone for my business, so I can't be without a working phone for very long. I was told that the battery was in stock and could be replaced in 3-4 hours. When I dropped off the phone, the guy at the counter again told me that it would be fixed in 3-4 hours, but if something came up that caused a delay, he would definitely give us a call and let us know. They close at 5 on Sundays and I dropped it off at 12:30.
At 4:50 we still hadn't heard anything, so I called to check on it. I was told that because it was their short day, they hadn't gotten to it yet, but it would be done first thing Monday for sure. At 1:30 on Monday, still no call, so again I tried calling. The first 3 times I called, it went to voicemail but the mail box was full, so I couldn't leave a message. The next few times I called, it rang busy. I finally got in touch with someone, who told me that it would not be ready for about 48 hours.
I would have been fine with 24-48 hours if I had been told that up front. I could have made other arrangements for a phone.< /review>

< Text>
This place has good reviews, so I was excited to have a reputable place close by to get the cracked back glass on my Google Pixel 3 XL fixed.

Well, they did fix the back glass, but that was the only thing that they got right. Up until they worked on my phone, it has been flawless. The tech who returned my phone to me didn't even notice my screen was partially covered with some sort of adhesive. My screen protector was trashed in the process of them trying to clean it. Sloppy workmanship!

Worse yet, I realized later that day that the phone's camera no longer worked. Once I got them on the phone to tell them about the issue, they were quick to deny any responsibility, washed their hands of it in a matter of minutes, and recommended I pursue a warranty replacement with the manufacturer.

Is it possible that they weren't at fault? Maybe... but what do you think the chances are that my camera stops working due to a motherboard failure (their over-the-phone diagnosis) during the same span of hours that they worked on the phone?

At best, they do very sloppy work (re: my trashed screen protector), and quite possibly, their careless workmanship resulted in a phone that needed to be entirely replaced.

After my experience, I would certainly not recommend them for anything other than a last resort fix. I regret the entire experience.

Buyer beware!< /Text>

< Text>
I own a Galaxy note 8. 2 weeks ago I cracked the corner of my phone screen. I was at the cusp of pre-ordering the note 9 when It was brought to my attention that I had Asurion insurance through Verizon. As I finished filing my claim, I was offered the option to come to this location. Before deciding, i chose to ask a few questions regarding this store's process. I called the store two minutes until closing. A man named Devon greeted me and answered every question I could throw at him all while keeping me from feeling rushed (I kept him 5 minutes past closing). By the end of our conversation, I was confident that I could trust them with my repair.
Here's how the process went:
I finished filing the claim through Asurion.
Contacted Devon to ensure that the claim went through and scheduled a good drop off time.
Dropped off the phone the next day at 10:20am.
Went out to bowl 6 games to buy some time.
Returned at 12:30 to find my phone waiting to be picked up.

The process went incredibly smoothly. So smoothly that I don't think I'll ever need to purchase another phone case again. I also want to note that all of their Note 8 screen repairs come with much more than just the screen. Although my phone only suffered from screen damage, they replaced the entire screen, chassis, and battery with OEM Parts. The phone came back looking and feeling like I had just taken it out of it's box for the first time.

Also, I had asked Devon about the retention of my phone's IP rating and assured me that because they are certified by Samsung, the phone will not only remain Waterproof, but the warranty will remain as well.<//Text>

< Review>
in my humble opinion I would avoid this place.   I purchased a samsung S8 plus and had issue with the unit from the beginning.    when I got the unit repaired it was great! they were polite and did the work quickly.  At the end they stated that the manufacturer's warranty is in effect again,  as it was repaired by them, sealed and presure tested as  being repaired by an authorized repair center  for samsung.   That repair is what I consider to be sub par.

the Samsung website directly states that (Carrying an IP68 dust and water resistance rating. Based on test conditions of submersion in up to 1.5 meters of fresh water for up to 30 minutes.) my phone was submerged no more the 10 seconds and no more than a 1 foot of water, soon after retrieving it  the phone died.  If they pressure tested, I wouldn't be having to deal with this issue.

Upon calling Ubreakifix about this issue they said they wouldn't cover it and that I need to just buy a new phone.  after becoming pissed off and wondering what happened, I took a closer look at the phone and can see where the issue was.  The repair was poorly done based off the pictures provided.  there is a 2mm gap between the back of the phone and the main body were UbreakIfix repaired the phone.  I checked all 4 sides and there is only 1 side with this issue.  A 2mm gap is more than enough for water to get in, to give you an idea, my finger nail at the tip is 1mm thick.  Long story short, I had to pay $200 for my insurance to cover the unit and get a new Phone in the midst losing a ton of data that's non retrievable.  I will be sending the old phone back to the insurance co with less money in my pocket due to a very poor repair.    If I didn't have Insurance this would have been a 1000$ mistake on their end as it is, i'm still out $200.  Take my opinion for what you want, I would have seeked somewhere else if I was given the option.

Addendum to my review.
I'm impressed that notes were taken about about my phone call.   so I need to clarify.  the original repair was for a cracked screen on the back  of the phone,  the repair had nothing to do with any water damage at all.  the phone was only 77 days old so well with in the warranty time, so assuming the repair was correctly done I took a chance on the IP68 rating by standing on the side of the pool, reached my hand in the pool with the phone and took a picture of my son passing his swim test.  most people would assume that its waterproof but I know IP68 ment a limited depth for a limited of time, not waterproof.  with that being said a depth of less the 1 foot for a time of 5 to 7 sec, one would feel comfortable with the IP68 rating. as the rating is up to 1.5 meters for up to 30 minutes,  the caveat in this is that there was a small gap wear the  glass back of the phone was replaced. thus being the likely culprit for the phone failure.  In the end, Yes I took a chance knowing I was in the safe limits of the phone  and I Paid dearly for that chance. In my decision of taking that chance, I wasnt counting on the  phone not being up to par after a repair.   There should have been no reason why the phone shouldn't have stood up to the conditions that I exposed them to.  In the end regardless, I'm the one that took the chance and paid the price for everything, but that doesn't stop HOW I FEEL that the repair of the unit wasn't correctly done leading to the high probability that  the leak originated from the repair site. I will contact insurance and ask them for the report of the damage to the phone,  If I'm in the wrong, I will take down this post and admit it but it will stay up if it's the reason.  To be honest I hate using this types of forums to deal with these issues.< /Review>
